  Got some new hardware, new math, re-encoded from laserdisc with S-VHS and
optical audio cables.
  Deep Red (1994) starring Michael Biehn, John de Lancie, Joanna Pacula.
  The movie itself is pretty standard "B" fare, but I simply like the concept
of nanobots, they are employed gratuitously in this flick :). The audio is
nice and clean, the laserdisc has a couple of minor flaws that show up,
briefly, once or twice in the flick - nothing serious, but not perfect.
